## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 High-Level BLoC Architecture (Mermaid Block Diagram)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    UI[Flutter UI Widgets] -->|add Event| EP[Event Sink]
    EP --> B[BLoC Business Logic]
    B -->|emit State| ST[Stream of States]
    ST --> BB[BlocBuilder]
    ST --> BL[BlocListener]
    BB --> UI
    BL --> SS[Side Effects: Snackbars, Navigation]
    BP[BlocProvider] -->|Creates and Injects| B
    BP --> UI
```

### 4.2 Detailed Event-to-State Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Interaction - Tap Button] --> B[Dispatch Event via context.read]
    B --> C[Event enters Bloc EventSink]
    C --> D{Event Router - on handler}
    D --> E[Execute Business Logic]
    E --> F{Async Operation?}
    F -->|No| G[Compute New State]
    F -->|Yes| H[Call API or DB]
    H --> G
    G --> I[Call emit newState]
    I --> J[Push to Stream]
    J --> K[BlocBuilder Receives State]
    J --> L[BlocListener Receives State]
    K --> M[UI Rebuilds]
    L --> N[Side Effect Triggered]
```

### 4.3 BLoC Widget Tree Integration Pattern

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Root[MaterialApp] --> BP[BlocProvider - CounterBloc]
    BP --> Home[HomePage Widget]
    Home --> BB[BlocBuilder - CounterBloc]
    BB --> T1[Text Widget showing value]
    Home --> FAB1[FAB - dispatches IncrementPressed]
    Home --> FAB2[FAB - dispatches DecrementPressed]
    BP -. Injects .-> BB
    FAB1 -. add Event .-> BP
    FAB2 -. add Event .-> BP
```

### 4.4 Cubit vs BLoC Comparison Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph CubitFlow[CU WORKFLOW]
        C1[UI calls cubit.method] --> C2[Cubit executes logic]
        C2 --> C3[emit state]
        C3 --> C4[Stream pushes to UI]
    end
    subgraph BlocFlow[BL WORKFLOW]
        B1[UI calls bloc.add Event] --> B2[Event enters handler]
        B2 --> B3[Handler executes logic]
        B3 --> B4[emit state]
        B4 --> B5[Stream pushes to UI]
    end
```

### 4.5 State Lifecycle of an Async BLoC Operation

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Initial
    Initial --> Loading: add LoadDataEvent
    Loading --> Success: Data fetched
    Loading --> Failure: Error thrown
    Success --> Loading: Refresh Event
    Failure --> Loading: Retry Event
    Success --> [*]: bloc.close
    Failure --> [*]: bloc.close
    Loading --> [*]: bloc.close
```

