# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. `[KTU University Exam - Dec 2023, Model QP]`
**Differentiate between `Navigator.push()` and `Navigator.pushReplacement()`. When would you choose one over the other?**

**Model Answer (3 marks)**:
- `Navigator.push()` **adds** a new route on top of the stack, increasing its depth by 1. Pressing back returns to the previous route. (1 mark)
- `Navigator.pushReplacement()` **replaces** the current top route with a new one; the stack depth remains unchanged. The replaced route is disposed, and its state is lost. (1 mark)
- **Use case distinction**: `push` is used for typical forward navigation (Home → Details). `pushReplacement` is used when you want to **prevent going back** to the source screen, e.g., Splash → Login, or after successful login → Dashboard, where the user should not be able to navigate "back" into the splash/login. (1 mark)

### Q2. `[KTU University Exam - May 2024, Model QP]`
**Explain the role of `RouteSettings.arguments` in named-route navigation. How is it accessed in the destination screen?**

**Model Answer (3 marks)**:
- `RouteSettings.arguments` is an `Object?` field used to carry arbitrary data alongside a named route push. (1 mark)
- It is supplied at the push site: `Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/details', arguments: myData);` (1 mark)
- In the destination screen, it is retrieved via `ModalRoute.of(context)!.settings.arguments`. The cast to the appropriate type is the developer's responsibility. (1 mark)

