### Question B (14 Marks) `[KTU University Exam - May 2024, Model QP]`

**(a)** What are **named routes** in Flutter? Compare the static `routes:` map approach with the dynamic `onGenerateRoute` callback. Provide example code snippets for both. **(7 marks)**

**(b)** Write a Flutter program to demonstrate **backward data passing** — a `HomeScreen` that pushes a `ColorPickerScreen`, the user picks a color, and on `pop` the chosen color is applied as the background of `HomeScreen`. Use named routes with `pushNamed` and `await`. **(7 marks)**

#### Model Solution

**(a) Named Routes Explanation (7 marks)**:

**Named routes** are string identifiers (e.g., `'/home'`, `'/profile'`) registered in the `MaterialApp` configuration. Instead of constructing a `MaterialPageRoute` manually, you push by name: `Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/profile')`. The framework resolves the name to a widget builder. (2 marks)

**Static `routes:` map**:
- Declared as `Map<String, WidgetBuilder>` inside `MaterialApp`.
- Best for simple, non-parameterized mappings.
- No way to access route arguments — every push with the same name produces the *same* widget type. (1.5 marks)

```dart
MaterialApp(
  initialRoute: '/',
  routes: {
    '/'        : (context) => const HomeScreen(),
    '/profile' : (context) => const ProfileScreen(),
  },
);
```

**Dynamic `onGenerateRoute` callback**:
- Receives a `RouteSettings` object containing the route `name` and `arguments`.
- Can return different routes conditionally based on the name or arguments.
- Allows access to `settings.arguments` for runtime data passing. (1.5 marks)

```dart
MaterialApp(
  initialRoute: '/',
  onGenerateRoute: (settings) {
    switch (settings.name) {
      case '/':
        return MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => const HomeScreen());
      case '/profile':
        final userId = settings.arguments as String;
        return MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => ProfileScreen(userId: userId));
      default:
        return null;   // 404
    }
  },
);
```

**Comparison Summary** (2 marks):

| **Criterion** | **Static `routes`** | **`onGenerateRoute`** |
|---|---|---|
| Argument support | ❌ None | ✅ `settings.arguments` |
| Code verbosity | Low | Medium |
| Flexibility | Limited | High (conditionals, auth guards) |
| Use case | Simple, fixed navigation graph | Large apps, deep linking |

**(b) Backward Data Passing Code (7 marks)**:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() => runApp(const MyApp());

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      initialRoute: '/',
      onGenerateRoute: (settings) {
        if (settings.name == '/')      return MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => const HomeScreen(bg: Colors.white));
        if (settings.name == '/picker')return MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => const ColorPickerScreen());
        return null;
      },
    );
  }
}

class HomeScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  final Color bg;
  const HomeScreen({super.key, required this.bg});
  @override
  State<HomeScreen> createState() => _HomeScreenState();
}

class _HomeScreenState extends State<HomeScreen> {
  late Color currentBg;

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    currentBg = widget.bg;
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      backgroundColor: currentBg,
      appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('Home — Pick a Color')),
      body: Center(
        child: ElevatedButton.icon(
          icon: const Icon(Icons.color_lens),
          label: const Text('Pick Background Color'),
          onPressed: () async {
            // THE KEY LINE: await the push, receive the chosen Color
            final picked = await Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/picker') as Color?;
            if (picked != null && mounted) {
              setState(() => currentBg = picked);
            }
          },
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

class ColorPickerScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  const ColorPickerScreen({super.key});

  static const palette = [
    Colors.red, Colors.green, Colors.blue,
    Colors.orange, Colors.purple, Colors.teal,
  ];

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('Choose a Color')),
      body: GridView.count(
        crossAxisCount: 3,
        children: palette.map((c) {
          return GestureDetector(
            onTap: () => Navigator.pop(context, c),  // RETURN VALUE
            child: Container(margin: const EdgeInsets.all(8), color: c),
          );
        }).toList(),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

**Mark Allocation Breakdown**:
- `MaterialApp` with `initialRoute` and `onGenerateRoute`: **1.5 marks**
- `HomeScreen` as a `StatefulWidget` with `bg` state: **1.5 marks**
- `await Navigator.pushNamed` and `setState` on result: **2 marks**
- `ColorPickerScreen` with `Navigator.pop(context, c)` returning the value: **2 marks**

