# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 Complete Flutter HTTP Request Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Triggers Action in UI] --> B[State Method Calls Service]
    B --> C[API Service Function Executes]
    C --> D{Await http.get post delete}
    D -->|Success| E[Check statusCode 200 201 204]
    D -->|Network Error| F[Throw Exception]
    E -->|Valid| G[jsonDecode response body]
    G --> H[Map JSON to Model fromJson]
    H --> I[Return List of Product]
    I --> J[FutureBuilder Rebuilds UI]
    F --> K[Show Error Snackbar]
    E -->|Invalid| K
```

## 4.2 REST API Architecture — Client-Server Interaction

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph Client["Flutter Mobile App"]
        UI[UI Widget ListView]
        FB[FutureBuilder]
        SVC[ApiService]
        MOD[Product Model]
        UI --> FB
        FB --> SVC
        SVC --> MOD
    end

    subgraph Network["Internet HTTPS"]
        REQ[HTTP Request]
        RES[HTTP Response]
    end

    subgraph Server["Remote Server"]
        API[REST API Endpoint]
        DB[(Database)]
        API --> DB
    end

    SVC -->|1 Send Request| REQ
    REQ -->|2 Routed to| API
    API -->|3 Query Data| DB
    DB -->|4 Return Rows| API
    API -->|5 Build Response| RES
    RES -->|6 Return to Client| SVC
```

## 4.3 JSON Parsing Pipeline — String to Dart Object

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Raw JSON String from API] --> B[jsonDecode returns dynamic]
    B --> C[Type Cast as Map String dynamic]
    C --> D[Extract Individual Fields]
    D --> E[Cast Each Field to Correct Dart Type]
    E --> F[Construct Product Object via fromJson]
    F --> G[Store in List of Products]
