### **Q2. [KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]**
**What is the role of the `Content-Type: application/json` header in an HTTP POST request?**

**Model Answer:**
The `Content-Type: application/json` header informs the server that the **request body** is formatted as a **JSON string**. Without this header, the server may try to parse the body as form-encoded data (`x-www-form-urlencoded`) or plain text, leading to a **400 Bad Request** error. In Flutter, this header is set inside the `headers` map of the `http.post()` call.

