## 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **High-Density Revision Checklist — Networking in Flutter**

- [ ] **Networking** = enabling a Flutter app to talk to a remote server over HTTP/HTTPS.
- [ ] The `http` package is the **standard** for Flutter HTTP calls — import it with `as http`.
- [ ] `http.get(url)` is used to **read** data — no body required.
- [ ] `http.post(url, headers: ..., body: ...)` is used to **create** data — body is a JSON string.
- [ ] `http.delete(url)` is used to **remove** data — typically no body.
- [ ] **JSON** is the most common data format for REST APIs.
- [ ] `jsonEncode()` converts Dart `Map`/`List` → JSON **String**.
- [ ] `jsonDecode()` converts JSON **String** → Dart `Map<String, dynamic>` or `List<dynamic>`.
- [ ] Always **cast** the result of `jsonDecode` — e.g., `as Map<String, dynamic>`.
- [ ] Always include the header `Content-Type: application/json` when sending JSON bodies.
- [ ] **Status codes to remember:** `200` (OK), `201` (Created), `204` (No Content), `404` (Not Found), `500` (Server Error).
- [ ] Use `async/await` and `try/catch` for **all** network calls.
- [ ] A **Model class** with a `factory fromJson()` constructor is the KTU-approved way to parse JSON.
- [ ] `FutureBuilder<T>` is the idiomatic widget for rendering async data in the UI.
- [ ] **Idempotent methods** (`GET`, `PUT`, `DELETE`) produce the same result on repeated calls.
- [ ] **Safe methods** (`GET`, `HEAD`) do not modify server state.
- [ ] Never call network methods inside `build()` — use `initState()` or event handlers.
- [ ] The free public API `https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com` is excellent for KTU lab exams.
- [ ] `dio` is an alternative to `http` with advanced features (interceptors, form-data, file upload) — for industry use.
- [ ] **REST** = architectural style; **RESTful API** = an API following REST principles.
