## 4.4 Diagram 4: Stream Architecture (Producer–Consumer with StreamController)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph P["PRODUCER (e.g., Timer, Sensor, Firebase)"]
        P1[Data Source]
    end

    P1 -- add data --> SC[StreamController\nfaucet]

    SC -- pushes --> ST[Stream\npipe]

    subgraph C["CONSUMER(S)"]
        L1[Listener 1\nWidget A]
        L2[Listener 2\nWidget B]
    end

    ST -- broadcast --> L1
    ST -- broadcast --> L2

    SC -- close --> END[onDone fires]
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **KTU Exam Tip:** The `StreamController` is the **bridge** between the data source (which doesn't know about UI) and the consumer (which doesn't know about data generation). This is the **Observer Pattern** in action.

