## 4.6 Diagram 6: async/await Execution Flow (Non-Blocking)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant UI as Flutter UI Thread
    participant EL as Event Loop
    participant Net as Network (HTTP)

    UI->>EL: Call loadData() (async)
    EL->>EL: Execute sync code\nuntil 'await http.get(url)'
    EL->>Net: Initiate HTTP request\n(non-blocking)
    EL-->>UI: Yield control back\nUI remains responsive
    Note over UI: User can scroll,\ntap buttons, animations run

    Net-->>EL: Response received (later)
    EL->>EL: Enqueue microtask\nto resume function
    EL->>EL: Resume after 'await'\nwith response data
    EL->>UI: setState() → triggers rebuild
    UI->>UI: Display new data
```

> [!NOTE]
> **The crucial point:** Between the `await` and the response, the UI thread is **not frozen**. The Event Loop handles other events (animations, gestures) freely. This is the **entire reason** Flutter apps feel smooth.
