### Question 2 [KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]

> **What is the role of the `await` keyword in Dart? Is `await` blocking? Justify your answer with an example.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

The `await` keyword is used inside an `async` function to **pause execution of that function** until the awaited `Future` completes, and to extract its resolved value. 

**`await` is NOT blocking.** *(1 mark)*

**Justification with example:** *(2 marks)*

```dart
Future<void> demo() async {
  print('A');
  await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 2));  // PAUSE local fn only
  print('B');  // runs after 2s, but UI thread was free in between
}
```

During the 2-second delay, the Dart Event Loop continues processing other events (gestures, animations, other timers), so the UI remains responsive. **Only the local function `demo()` is paused — the entire program is NOT blocked.**

