## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Where KTU students LOSE MARKS on this topic:**
>
> 1. **Saying `await` is "blocking"** — IT IS NOT. The Event Loop is free; only the local function pauses. (-2 marks)
> 2. **Forgetting `async` keyword** on a function that uses `await` — compilation error. (-1 mark)
> 3. **Calling `.listen()` twice on a single-subscription stream** — runtime `StateError`. Must use `asBroadcastStream()`. (-1 mark)
> 4. **Not calling `subscription.cancel()`** in `dispose()` of a StatefulWidget — memory leak. (-1 mark)
> 5. **Confusing `Future.error()` with throwing an error** — both work but `throw` is preferred in `async` functions. (-0.5 marks)
> 6. **Sequential `await`s that should be parallel** — use `Future.wait([...])` for independent ops. (-1 mark)
> 7. **Missing `try`/`catch`** around `await` — uncaught errors crash the isolate. (-2 marks)
> 8. **Not closing the `StreamController`** — triggers analyzer warning and memory leak. (-1 mark)

