### 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mark-Deduction Pitfalls in Module 4 (Testing & Debugging):**
>
> 1. **Confusing Widget Test with Integration Test** — Examiners deduct **2–3 marks** if a student runs a widget test on a real device or says integration tests use `WidgetTester`. Remember: widget tests use a *test harness*, integration tests use a *real device*.
> 2. **Forgetting `tester.pump()`** — When the test snippet lacks `pump()` after `setState`, the examiner deducts **1 mark** for "incomplete test logic".
> 3. **Mentioning `print()` as the best debugging tool** — Examiners expect DevTools + breakpoints as *primary* tools; `print` is *secondary*. Phrase as: "I use `print` for quick checks, but for production-grade debugging I rely on DevTools."
> 4. **Skipping the Test Pyramid in Question A** — The pyramid diagram is a **mandatory 2-mark** component. Drawing it without the three labels loses marks.
> 5. **Mixing Hot Reload and Hot Restart** — State-preservation is the *defining* difference. Confusing them costs **2 marks**.
> 6. **No `pubspec.yaml` mention in integration tests** — Examiners expect a note that `integration_test` SDK must be added under `dev_dependencies`.

