### 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid-Revision Checklist)

> [!TIP]
> **High-Density Last-Minute Revision — Module 4: Testing & Debugging**

- 🔹 Flutter has **3 testing layers**: Unit, Widget, Integration — arranged in a **Test Pyramid**.
- 🔹 **Unit tests** test pure functions/classes in isolation; no UI, no Flutter framework; **fastest**; use `test()` and `expect()`.
- 🔹 **Widget tests** render a single widget via `testWidgets()` and `WidgetTester.pumpWidget()`; verify UI and interactions.
- 🔹 **Integration tests** run the full app on a real device/emulator; use `package:integration_test`; **slowest** but **highest confidence**.
- 🔹 Key widget-test commands: `tester.pump()`, `tester.pumpAndSettle()`, `tester.tap()`, `tester.enterText()`, `tester.drag()`.
- 🔹 Finders: `find.byKey()`, `find.byType()`, `find.text()`, `find.byIcon()`.
- 🔹 AAA Pattern: **Arrange → Act → Assert** — universal testing structure.
- 🔹 `setUp()` / `tearDown()` hooks run before/after each test for shared fixtures.
- 🔹 **Dart DevTools** = the most powerful debugging suite (Widget Inspector, Memory, Timeline, Network, Logging).
- 🔹 **Breakpoints** allow line-by-line step debugging (Step Over `F10`, Step Into `F11`).
- 🔹 **`print()` / `debugPrint()`** — simplest, lowest-overhead debugging.
- 🔹 **Hot Reload (`r`)** = sub-1s UI update, **state preserved**; **Hot Restart (`R`)** = full restart, state reset.
- 🔹 **Profile mode** (`flutter run --profile`) for performance debugging — no debug overhead, full profiling hooks.
- 🔹 **Flutter Inspector "Select Widget Mode"** — click any widget on screen to see its properties.
- 🔹 Test command: `flutter test <path>`; integration: `flutter test integration_test/`.
- 🔹 Test files must end in `*_test.dart` for auto-discovery.
- 🔹 Test coverage: `flutter test --coverage` → generates `lcov.info`.
- 🔹 **Mocking** (`mockito`) is used to replace external dependencies in unit tests.
- 🔹 **Mnemonic "UWI-D"** — Unit, Widget, Integration, Debugging — the 4 pillars of Module 4.
- 🔹 **Common Exam Trap:** Widget tests do **not** run on a real device; integration tests do.

